{"title_page": "2011 Toronto International Film Festival", "text_new": "{{Infobox Film Festival\n| name           = 2011 Toronto International Film Festival\n| image          = 2011 Toronto International Film Festival poster.jpg\n| caption        = Festival poster\n| host           = Toronto International Film Festival Group\n| number         = Over 200 feature films<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/tiff_list_2011_the_announced_toronto_film_festival_lineup/|title=TIFF List 2011: A Complete Guide To The Toronto International Film Festival|accessdate=October 19, 2013}}</ref> \n| opening        = ''[[From the Sky Down]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news2/interactives/tiff-openers/|title=TIFF: A history of opening nights|accessdate=October 19, 2013 | work=CBC News}}</ref> \n| closing        = ''[[Page Eight]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.criticizethis.ca/2011/08/tiff-2011-announces-closing-night-film-and-final-lineup-of-galas-and-special-presentations.html |title=TIFF 2011 announces closing night film and final lineup of Galas and Special Presentations |accessdate=October 19, 2013 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130329173835/http://www.criticizethis.ca/2011/08/tiff-2011-announces-closing-night-film-and-final-lineup-of-galas-and-special-presentations.html |archivedate=March 29, 2013 |df= }}</ref> \n| location       = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]\n| language       = English\n| date           = {{Start date|2011|09|08}}\u2013{{End date|2011|09|18}}\n| website        = [http://tiff.net/ tiff.net]\n}}\n\nThe 36th annual '''[[Toronto International Film Festival]]''' (TIFF) was held in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]] between September 8 and September 18, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tiff.net/pdfs/TIFF%20Annual%20Report%202011.pdf |title=2011 Toronto International Film Festival Annual report |accessdate=October 11, 2013 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120617012923/http://tiff.net/pdfs/TIFF%20Annual%20Report%202011.pdf |archivedate=June 17, 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name=thefestival>{{cite press release |url=http://www.tiff.net/thefestival |title=The Festival |date=2011-03-01 |accessdate=2011-03-01}}</ref>\n[[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] was selected to be showcased for the 2011 City to City programme.<ref name=\"Toronto International Film Festival Selects Buenos Aires As 2011 City To City Selection\">{{cite press release |url=http://www.tiff.net/press/pressreleases/2011/ctc11 |title=Toronto International Film Festival Selects Buenos Aires As 2011 City To City Selection |date=2011-02-08 |accessdate=2011-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110312073012/http://tiff.net/press/pressreleases/2011/ctc11 |archive-date=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead|df= }}</ref> The opening film was ''[[From the Sky Down]]'', a documentary film about the band [[U2]], directed by [[Davis Guggenheim]].<ref name=\"BBCU2\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-14308535 |title=U2 documentary to open Toronto Film Festival |accessdate=2011-07-28 |work=BBC News |date=2011-07-27| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110728001915/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-14308535| archivedate= 28 July 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| url-status= live}}</ref> Considerable media attention at the time focused on Madonna's behaviour during the festival.\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award<ref name=\"awards\">{{cite web|url=http://tiff.net/thefestival/about/awards/awards2011 |title=TIFF: Awards 2011 |accessdate=2011-09-28 |work=tiff.net |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923174431/http://tiff.net/thefestival/about/awards/awards2011 |archivedate=2011-09-23 |df= }}</ref>\n! Film\n! Director\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Drama)\n| ''[[Where Do We Go Now?]]''\n| [[Nadine Labaki]]\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Drama), First Runner Up\n| ''[[Starbuck (film)|Starbuck]]''\n| [[Ken Scott (writer)|Ken Scott]]''\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Drama), Second Runner Up\n| ''[[A Separation]]''\n| [[Asghar Farhadi]]\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Documentary)\n| ''[[The Island President]]''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.maldivestraveller.mv/news/international/the-island-president-predominates-international-festival/2674/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923213008/http://www.maldivestraveller.mv/news/international/the-island-president-predominates-international-festival/2674/ |archive-date=2011-09-23 |url-status=dead|df= }}</ref>\n| [[Jon Shenk]]\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Documentary), First Runner Up\n| ''[[First Position]]''\n| [[Bess Kargman]]\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Documentary), Second Runner Up\n| ''[[Pearl Jam 20]]'' \n| [[Cameron Crowe]]\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Midnight Madness)\n| ''[[The Raid (2011 film)|The Raid]]''\n| [[Gareth Evans (director)|Gareth Evans]]\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Midnight Madness), First Runner Up\n| ''[[You're Next]]''\n| [[Adam Wingard]]\n|-\n| People's Choice Award (Midnight Madness), Second Runner Up\n| ''[[God Bless America (film)|God Bless America]]''\n| [[Bobcat Goldthwait]]\n|-\n| Best Canadian Feature Film\n| ''[[Monsieur Lazhar]]''\n| [[Philippe Falardeau]]\n|-\n| Best Canadian First Feature Film\n| ''[[Citizen Gangster]]''\n| [[Nathan Morlando]]\n|- \n| Best Canadian Short Film\n| ''[[Doubles with Slight Pepper]]''\n| [[Ian Harnarine]]\n|- \n| FIPRESCI Special Presentations\n| ''[[The First Man (film)|The First Man]]''\n| [[Gianni Amelio]]\n|-\n| FIPRESCI Discovery\n| ''[[Avalon (2011 film)|Avalon]]''\n| [[Axel Peters\u00e9n]] \n|}\n\n==Programmes==\n\n===Gala Presentations===\n*''[[Albert Nobbs]]'' by [[Rodrigo Garc\u00eda (director)|Rodrigo Garc\u00eda]]\n*''[[The Awakening (2011 film)|The Awakening]]'' by [[Nick Murphy (director)|Nick Murphy]]\n*''[[Beloved (2011 film)|Beloved]]'' by [[Christophe Honor\u00e9]]\n*''[[Butter (2011 film)|Butter]]'' by [[Jim Field Smith